 @junedmomin2106  watch very carefully the drone shot and Sainz's onboard:
Sainz is going straight and does NOT turn his steering wheel
Perez is drifting slightly rightwards - watch the drone shot and look at the gap closing as Perez comes alongside. All Checo had to do was go parallel to Sainz and it would have been fine

 @junedmomin2106  It's not about track limits. The rule require Max to give space to Norris inside the track, not within track limits. That means enough space between him and the line for Norris. You really should read the rule before commenting. 

Also, neither Sainz not Perez swerved. Sainz was drifting back on track after his wide corner, while Perez was going straight. Neither car made any moves until they collide. Perez takes on more fault because both cars did not do anything wrong, but Perez can see and avoid the collision better than Sainz can, though it doesn't mean it's Perez's fault. 

On Lando's case, it was completely Verstappen's fault, but Norris is allowed to take evasive action. He isn't responsible for the collision when Verstappen is the one that broke the rules, though. He just have to take L on losing the podium or even potential win by not avoiding.

